# Planning Stage Freeze Guard

When user asks for planning, auditing, or "next steps", apply these constraints before execution:

## Hard Limits
- Do not launch more than 2 subagents during planning stage.
- Do not read or scan giant generated artifacts (for example: `node_modules`, `dist`, build intermediates, large `.ipynb` outputs) unless user explicitly requests.
- Prefer targeted path scopes over repo-wide scans.

## Planning Workflow
- First return a short plan with scoped modules.
- Execute in small batches only after confirming scope.
- Avoid parallel shell + parallel subagent at the same time in planning stage.

## Exclusions (default)
- `**/node_modules/**`
- `**/dist/**`
- `**/android/app/build/**`
- `**/*executed.ipynb`

